name: Spaghettification
description: When you cross the event horizon of a black hole, you, along with all other information begin a wonka-like stretching process which postulates that you become thinner and longer (not necessarily being aware of it), rotating around the rim of a one way ticket (to another universe ? to be one part of the informational content of a new [littlebigbang] universe ? / popping out of a white hole somewhere else) until you begin to slip down the actual hole we can't see. I love black holes, the one thing we don't really understand, along with what is consciousness, how do we know what reality is ? Are there more than 4 dimensions, is travel faster than C possible, what do strings look like.. ad infinitum, is there a highest number, would gettin rid of infinity help, could the universe be infinite anyway
